						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I think hardly anyone uses NESHLA... =)</div>
<br />
<br />That's because it was windows only and the documentation was missing some key pieces.  I have begun rectifying the situation.  I fixed a ton of portability issues with NESHLA and ported it to Linux/Mac OS X/Cygwin.  You can get it here: <a href="http://bitbucket.org/wookie/neshla/downloads/" class="postlink">http://bitbucket.org/wookie/neshla/downloads/</a>
<br />
<br />I have also ported all of the original documentation over to a wiki and filled in a lot of the missing pieces here: <a href="http://bitbucket.org/wookie/neshla/wiki/NESHLA_Programming_Manual" class="postlink">http://bitbucket.org/wookie/neshla/wiki/NESHLA_Programming_Manual</a>
